lor: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">You&#=
8217;ll notice, though, while you&#8217;re exploring, that not every artist=
 or work is in the database. To ensure accuracy and consistency, and to gen=
erate a return metric, Masterworks doesn&#8217;t include paintings that hav=
en&#8217;t been sold at auction at least twice.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color:=
 #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">For examp=
le, when I read about <em>Salvator Mundi</em>, I obviously searched Leonard=
o da Vinci, but came up empty-handed. I thought there was an error, so I re=
ached out to Jason Papodopoulos, who runs data science at Masterworks to as=
k about the omission. His answer was more fascinating than I could have hop=
ed for, and I&#8217;ll repost it here in full:&nbsp;</p><blockquote style=
=3D"border-left: 4px solid #67bdfc; margin: 1em 0;"><p style=3D"color: #1a1=
a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0; margin-left: 1e=
m;"><em>Regarding da Vinci, <strong>we have not identified any da Vinci auc=
tion results</strong> except </em>Salvator Mundi<em>, meaning not even work=
s that have been sold once. We have, however, identified multiple works by =
followers or artists of his circle. <strong>His works never come at auction=
, and when they do, you see what happens.</strong></em></p><p style=3D"colo=
r: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0; margin-l=
eft: 1em;"><em>In the case of Salvator Mundi (see: <a href=3D"https://email=
=2Emg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkMGOhCAMhp9muG=
koKqMHDnvZ1zAIdYYMggtV17dfxjls0rRJmz9=
f-hlN-IjpVGvMxN5tpHNFFfDIHokwsS1jGp1VIEXfdO3ArGot9F3PXB7nhLho5xWlDdm6Td4ZTS=
6GK8G56NhTcaFNK9pJDOZuhrkdeINz3_ec39upl_OHqzfrMBhUuGM6Y0Dm1ZNozbfm6ya-Sx3HU=
Ztncpkc5trEpex8pE-vPMagk42V1dXugnEVtJ2ooIOhytrvmmKqli1YV0kA3smmBJlTggvgIACa=
Drisoea_P_srHI1bYL61fHmIOm9TJm1ebyhLKkSaYnLhUc6vp17QX4fy_lhmYTg6Rwx68mg_Zug=
j-HI1PjBgKuLtqKloBRDNnUv5dnuZKOoakP0gObBCtrGkwj_0D0Nhkms" style=3D"color: #=
1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">Christie&#8217;s</a> ), its Provenance=
 (list of prior ownership) does mention 2 public sales. One may think that =
this makes the work a repeat-sale pair. However, a major factor in the Old =
Masters market is <strong>attribution</strong> and <strong>authentication</=
strong>. In the past, the work was attributed to Giovanni Antonio Boltraffi=
o, and <strong>was sold for &#163;45</strong>. After research, <a href=3D"h=
ttps://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkE2OgzAMhU_T7Iri_FC6yGI2cw0UEheiQsIkpgy=
3n5QuRrJsyU_20_ucJRxTPsyaCrF36-lY0UTcy4xEmNlWMPfBG2hFJ7W6M2-Uh053LJT-kREXG2=
ZDeUO2bsMcnKWQ4nnBudBsMlarm3ZOoPRCDNY9VKfghl5aZUE7__G1mw8YHRp8YT5SRDabiWgtF=
_l1Ed-19n1vaErbOJFLjUtL3RU7vyylfF226MMVOik6YMEILoCDAJAaeNtAw39_Xs-4y7DA46L4=
MoqmbEMh657vVyybmGhIOcSxys_JLjifQg3V11n_Bzp6jHaY0X_y0gfbSaAfMWKuOH1vqcICEPL=
G2_ZN7MxXgUhou3vLgVVnn-pV_Df9AwpOhmM" style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; text-decorat=
ion: underline;">specialists concluded</a> that it was actually a da Vinci.=
 Hence, the assumption that you can calculate the return of a work because =
an artwork doesn't change is challenged in such cases.&nbsp;</em></p><p sty=
le=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0=
; margin-left: 1em;"><em>Under our research framework, we do not include wo=
rks that faced issues with attribution and/or authentication. This is one o=
f the reasons why we are also not involved in the Old Masters market.</em><=
/p></blockquote><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 2=
6px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">There&#8217;s so much in that answer. No da Vinci =
painting has <em>ever </em>changed hands twice in a public auction, and <em=
>Salvator Mundi</em> is the only known da Vinci to sell at auction. That ex=
plains why it was the most expensive sale of all-time. The only other time =
the work went up for sale at auction, it was actually under another artist&=
#8217;s name, which allowed it to slip under the radar and sell for &#163;4=
5. Once da Vinci was confirmed as the artist, the <strong>price shot up ove=
r 7 million times!</strong></p><div class=3D"captioned-image-container-stat=
